frameDefinitions: These are words describing situations in which a Perpetrator takes Goods from a  Victim or a Source.
An Agent manipulates a Sound_maker or a Cause causes the Sound_maker to emit a sound.
A Protagonist performs some Action without fully considering the circumstances under which he or she acts, or the possibly (negative) consequences of the Action.
An Assailant physically attacks a Victim (which is usually but not always sentient), causing or intending to cause the Victim physical damage.
These are words describing situations in which a Perpetrator wrongs a Victim by taking something (Goods) from them.
An Ingestor consumes food or drink (Ingestibles), which entails putting the Ingestibles in the mouth for delivery to the digestive system.
frameExamples: I can't believe he <t>pickpocketed</t> my gold watch !
The monks would <t>ring</t> the bell until sundown.
Would it be a little <t>impatient</t> of me to ask when an album might appear?
As soon as he stepped out of the bar he was <t>set</t> upon by four men in ski-masks.
Half of the team <t>held</t> <t>up</t> the tellers while the others were stationed to report the arrival of police.
listRoleDefinitions: <fen>Perpetrator</fen> is the person (or other agent) that takes the goods away.
<fen>Victim</fen> is the person (or other sentient being or group) that owns the goods before they are taken away by the perpetrator.
<fen>Goods</fen> is anything (including labor, time, or legal rights) that can be taken away.
<fen>Source</fen> is the initial location of the goods, before they change location.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the theft occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the theft occurs.
The individual that manipulates a Sound_maker so that it makes Noise.
The entity that produces the Noise, as a result of the action of the Agent.
The inanimate force of nature that causes the <fen>Sound_maker</fen> to produce noise.
The time at which the noise is produced.
The location at which the sound is produced.
The <fen>Protagonist</fen> acts or is apt to act with some degree of consideration regarding the circumstances and possible consequences of an <fen>Action</fen> he or she may perform.
The <fen>Action</fen> is carried out by the <fen>Protagonist</fen> with or without regard for the circumstances under which it is performed or consideration of possible consequences.
The period of time when the <fen>Protagonist</fen> acts with (or without) consideration regarding an <fen>Action</fen>.
This role is the being or entity that is injured by the <fen>Assailant</fen>'s attack.
The person (or other self-directed entity) that is attempting physical harm to the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Assailant</fen> attacks the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Assailant</fen> makes an assault on the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The <fen>Perpetrator</fen> is the person (or other agent) that takes the <fen>Goods</fen> away by force or threats.
The <fen>Victim</fen> is the person (or other sentient being or group) that owns the <fen>Goods</fen> before they are taken away by the <fen>Perpetrator</fen>.
Source is the initial location of the goods, before they change location.
The <fen>Time</fen> indicates when the Robbery occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the Robbery occurs.
The <fen>Ingestor</fen> is the person eating or drinking.
The <fen>Ingestibles</fen> are the entities that are being consumed by the <fen>Ingestor</fen>.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.

Leslie STOLE the watch from Kim <fex>in the park</fex>.

<fex>What he did</fex> was impetuous and quite irrational - some might say ill-considered.
Were n't you impetuous <fex>when you were young</fex>?

<fex>The mysterious fighter</fex> attacked the guardsmen with a sabre.
